did.abstract: Records consist of correspondence, reports, bidding records, and other documents related to architecture work and construction.

bioghist.head: History:
bioghist.p: An University Architect has served as the construction officer of Washington State University from 1911 onward. The modern form of the office dates from 1947, when it became a full-time, staffed administrative department. In 1967, the office was renamed as Facilities Planning and later as Facilities Development. It is responsible for the major construction projects of the university.

scopecontent.p: The records consist of correspondence, reports, bidding records, and other documents related to architecture work and construction.

arrangement.p: Records of the University Architect/Facilities Planning are arranged according the building number system that identifies structures owned by Washington State University. The archival arrangement of the records follows the office practice without variance.
Locating records revenant to a specific project or building requires having the building number available.

accessrestrict.p: The Collection is open for research use.

acqinfo.p: This portion of the University Architect/Facilities Planning building file was transferred to university archives in 1981 (UA81-11) and 1982 (UA82-09), in accordance with approved records schedules.

processinfo.p: The records were processed by Ann Klavano in March 1983, and the descriptions were expanded and enhanced by Brenda Jackson in September, 2000
